Linux, Drupal and Mozilla are only a few examples of successful open source projects. Despite this there are still a lot of people in the industry who have reservations against open source. The general concern of most of these sceptics is why would anyone choose to work for free? 

I work for GoalGorilla, a leading Drupal agency that is deeply involved in the Drupal community and funds the core team of Open Social. This distribution was developed completely open source, so when we asked the Drupal community for help of course we had to ask ourselves how we could motivate people to get involved.', 1, '2018-09-06 10:59:21', 1260, 38); 
